    {
      "type": "review",
      "id": 4024256235,
      "user": "gemini-code-assist[bot]",
      "state": "COMMENTED",
      "body": "## Code Review\n\nThis pull request refactors the error reporting logic for the FAIL_FAST failure mode in the Temporal workflow execution stage. It replaces a complex string construction with distinct ValueError messages, improving clarity when a failure message is available. The associated integration and unit tests have been updated to match the new error string format. I have no feedback to provide.",
      "created_at": "2026-03-28T00:11:22Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-28T00:11:22Z",
      "url": "https://github.com/MoonLadderStudios/MoonMind/pull/1022#pullrequestreview-4024256235"
    },
    {
      "type": "review_comment",
      "id": 3003751402,
      "user": "Copilot",
      "body": "The raised message hard-codes \"execution failed\" whenever `failure_message` is non-empty, even if `result_status` is something else (e.g. CANCELLED is handled elsewhere in the codebase). This can produce misleading errors. Consider including `result_status` in the message (and avoid hard-coding \"failed\"), e.g. \"plan node execution returned status <STATUS>: <failure_message>\" or similar.\n```suggestion\n                            raise ValueError(\n                                f\"plan node execution returned status {result_status}: {failure_message}\"\n                            )\n```",
      "created_at": "2026-03-28T00:11:35Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-03-28T00:11:35Z",
      "url": "https://github.com/MoonLadderStudios/MoonMind/pull/1022#discussion_r3003751402",
