    {
      "type": "review",
      "id": 4024256910,
      "user": "copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]",
      "state": "COMMENTED",
      "body": "## Pull request overview\n\nRefactors `MoonMindRunWorkflow._run_execution_stage` error formatting so FAIL_FAST failures surface the underlying child execution failure message (instead of a generic \u201creturned status FAILED \u2026\u201d message), and updates tests to assert the new error text.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Update FAIL_FAST exception message to prefer the activity-reported failure message.\n- Adjust unit/integration tests to match the new exception format.\n\n### Reviewed changes\n\nCopilot reviewed 3 out of 3 changed files in this pull request and generated 1 comment.\n\n| File | Description |\n| ---- | ----------- |\n| `moonmind/workflows/temporal/workflows/run.py` | Changes ValueError formatting to surface the child failure message when available. |\n| `tests/unit/workflows/temporal/test_run_artifacts.py` | Updates regex match to assert the new surfaced failure message. |\n| `tests/integration/workflows/temporal/workflows/test_run.py` | Updates assertion to check for the new failure message in the propagated Temporal ApplicationError. |\n\n\n\n\n\n---\n\n\ud83d\udca1 <a href=\"/MoonLadderStudios/MoonMind/new/main?filename=.github/instructions/*.instructions.md\" class=\"Link--inTextBlock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Add Copilot custom instructions</a> for smarter, more guided reviews. <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/customizing-copilot/adding-repository-custom-instructions-for-github-copilot\" class=\"Link--inTextBlock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Learn how to get started</a>.",
